title: High school football stat leaders
text:
High school football stat leaders Originally published October 16, 2015 at 6:11 pm Here's the Top 5 in each category. By Solange Reyner 
Here’s the Top 5 in each category. For full list of player stats, click here. If a player is missing from our list, it’s likely because we have not received stats from the coaches. All stats need to be sent in to preps@seattletimes.com by Monday afternoon. 
Passing 1. Harley Kirsch, Eastside Catholic – 1,859 yards, 17 TDs, 2 INT 2. Gresch Jensen, Auburn Mountainview – 1,762 yards, 23 TDs, 6 INT 3. Camron Humphrey, Issaquah – 1,608 yards, 15 TDs, 4 INT 4. Jacob Eason, Lake Stevens – 1,553 yards, 16 TDs, 2 INT 5. Bryce Missey, Bethel – 1,523 yards, 21 TDs, 5 INT 
Rushing 1. Kenneth Turner, Jefferson – 914 yards, 12 TDs 2. Tariq Ellis, Washington – 854 yards, 9 TDs 3. JJ Jerome, Monroe – 850 yards, 15 TDs 4. Connor Wedington, Sumner – 802 yards, 13 TDs 5. Antoine Patton Jr., Ballard – 781 yards, 16 TDs 
Receiving 1. Hunter Bryant, Eastside Catholic – 655 yards, 10 TDs 2. Tristan Beard, Curtis – 622 yards, 7 TDs 3. Tyler Torgerson, Puyallup – 615 yards, 5 TDs 4. Emmanuel Daigbe, Kent-Meridian – 568 yards, 5 TDs 5. Joe Nelson, Issaquah – 556 yards, 6 TDs Most Read Stories
